1457	\begin{lemma}[The rotated triple-overlap ring cocycle identity \(\Phi = \id\)]
1458	  \label{lem:gr_cocycle_phi_id}
1459	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Grassmannian.cocyclePhiId}
1460	  \uses{def:gr_cocycle_theta_ij, def:gr_away_mul_comm_equiv, lem:gr_cocycle_imageMatrix_eq,
1461	    lem:gr_cocycle}
1462	  \textit{The ring identity underlying the \(\mathrm{cocycle}\) field of the glue datum.}
1463	  Fix \(d \le r\) and three subsets \(I,J,K \subseteq \{1,\dots,r\}\) of cardinality \(d\). On the
1464	  triple-overlap chart ring \(R_{IJK} := \mathrm{Localization.Away}\,(\minordet_{I,J}\cdot\minordet_{I,K})\)
1465	  the composite ring endomorphism
1466	  \[
1467	    \Phi := \Theta_{I,J,K} \circ \mathrm{swap}_J \circ \Theta_{J,K,I} \circ \mathrm{swap}_K
1468	            \circ \Theta_{K,I,J} \circ \mathrm{swap}_I
1469	  \]
1470	  equals the identity \(\mathrm{RingHom.id}\,R_{IJK}\), where each \(\Theta_{X,Y,Z} =
1471	  \mathtt{cocycleΘIJ}\,d\,r\,X\,Y\,Z\) (\cref{def:gr_cocycle_theta_ij}, taken for the rotated index
1472	  triple) and each \(\mathrm{swap}_X\) is the matching order-swap algebra equivalence
1473	  \(\mathtt{awayMulCommEquiv}\) (\cref{def:gr_away_mul_comm_equiv}).
