1477	  Both endomorphisms are ring homomorphisms out of the localization
1478	  \(R_{IJK} = \mathrm{Localization.Away}\,(\minordet_{I,J}\cdot\minordet_{I,K})\), so by Mathlib's
1479	  \(\mathrm{IsLocalization.ringHom\_ext}\) for the submonoid generated by
1480	  \(\minordet_{I,J}\cdot\minordet_{I,K}\) it suffices to
1481	  check equality on the chart-ring generators (the images of the universal matrix entries). On those
1482	  generators \(\Phi\) unwinds, via the order-swaps and the \(\Theta\) definitions, to the rotated
