1491	
1492	\begin{definition}
1493	[The Grassmannian scheme \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\) over \(\mathbb{Z}\)]
1494	  \label{def:gr_glued_scheme}
1495	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Grassmannian.scheme}
1496	  \uses{def:gr_affine_chart, def:gr_transition, lem:gr_cocycle,
1497	    def:gr_chart_overlap, def:gr_chart_incl, lem:gr_chartIncl_isOpenImmersion,
1498	    lem:gr_chartIncl_self_isIso, def:gr_chart_transition,
1499	    lem:gr_chartTransition_self, def:gr_away_pullback_iso,
1500	    lem:gr_awayPullbackIso_inv_fst, lem:gr_awayPullbackIso_inv_snd,
1501	    def:gr_away_mul_comm_equiv, def:gr_cocycle_theta_ij,
1502	    def:gr_chart_transition', lem:gr_chartTransition'_fac,
1503	    lem:gr_chartTransition'_ringIdentity, lem:gr_cocycle_imageMatrix_eq,
1504	    lem:gr_cocycle_phi_id}
1505	  % NOTE (formalization status): the triple-overlap glue-datum fields are
1506	  % formalized and axiom-clean in Lean -- the `t'`-field
1507	  % (\cref{def:gr_chart_transition'}, Lean `chartTransition'`), its
1508	  % `t_fac`-compatibility (\cref{lem:gr_chartTransition'_fac}, Lean
1509	  % `chartTransition'_fac`), the underlying ring identity
1510	  % (\cref{lem:gr_chartTransition'_ringIdentity}, Lean
1511	  % `chartTransition'_ringIdentity`), and the order-swap helper
1512	  % (\cref{lem:gr_awayMulCommEquiv_comp_algebraMap}). NOT yet formalized: the
1513	  % `cocycle` field, the `Scheme.GlueData` bundle, and `Grassmannian.scheme`
1514	  % itself. The categorical reduction of `cocycle` is solved (the conjugating
1515	  % pullback isomorphisms telescope away); the residual is the rotated ring
1516	  % cocycle identity Phi = id detailed below. The
1517	  % \lean{...AlgebraicGeometry.Grassmannian.scheme} target above therefore does
1518	  % not yet exist in Lean.
1519	  % SOURCE: [Nitsure], \S 1, sub-section "Construction by gluing together
1520	  % affine patches" (read from
1521	  % references/nitsure-hilbert-quot-src/nitsure-hilbert-quot.tex, L843-L850).
1522	  % SOURCE QUOTE:
1523	  % "Therefore the schemes
1524	  %  $U^I$, as $I$ varies over all the
1525	  %  ${r\choose d}$ different
1526	  %  subsets of  $\{ 1,\ldots, r\}$ of cardinality $d$,
1527	  %  can be glued together by the co-cycle $(\theta_{I,J})$ to form a
1528	  %  finite-type scheme $\grass(r,d)$ over $\Z$. As each $U^I$ is
1529	  %  isomorphic to $\AA^{d(r-d)}_{\Z}$, it follows that
1530	  %  $\grass(r,d) \to \spec \Z$ is smooth of relative dimension $d(r-d)$."
1531	  \textit{Source: [Nitsure], \S 1.}
1532	  Gluing the affine charts \(\{U^I\}\) (\cref{def:gr_affine_chart}), one for each
1533	  of the \(\binom{r}{d}\) subsets \(I \subseteq \{1,\dots,r\}\) of cardinality
1534	  \(d\), along the open subschemes \(U^I_J \subseteq U^I\) via the transition
1535	  isomorphisms \(\theta_{I,J} : U^I_J \xrightarrow{\sim} U^J_I\)
1536	  (\cref{def:gr_transition}) -- which satisfy the cocycle condition
1537	  \(\theta_{I,K} = \theta_{J,K} \circ \theta_{I,J}\) and \(\theta_{I,I} = \id\)
1538	  of \cref{lem:gr_cocycle} -- yields a scheme
1539	  \[
1540	    \mathrm{Gr}(r,d) \longrightarrow \Spec \mathbb{Z}.
1541	  \]
1542	  It is of finite type over \(\mathbb{Z}\) (a finite gluing of finitely
1543	  generated \(\mathbb{Z}\)-algebras), and under the gluing each \(U^I\) is an
1544	  open subscheme of \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\) with \(U^I \cap U^J = U^I_J\).
1545	
1546	  \emph{Construction of the glue datum.} The gluing is carried out through the
1547	  Mathlib vehicle for scheme gluing, a glue datum in the sense of a category of
1548	  schemes (the structure \(\mathtt{Scheme.GlueData}\), extending the abstract
1549	  glue-datum interface). Its data are supplied as follows. The index set is the
1550	  set \(J := \{\, I \subseteq \{1,\dots,r\} : \#(I) = d \,\}\) of size-\(d\)
1551	  subsets. The objects are the charts \(U^I\) (\cref{def:gr_affine_chart}); the
1552	  pairwise overlaps are the schemes \(U^I_J\) (\cref{def:gr_chart_overlap}); the
1553	  inclusions \(f_{I,J} : U^I_J \to U^I\) are the open immersions
1554	  \(\cref{def:gr_chart_incl}\) (open immersions by
1555	  \cref{lem:gr_chartIncl_isOpenImmersion}, in particular monomorphisms), with the
1556	  identity field \(f_{\mathrm{id}}\) supplied by
1557	  \cref{lem:gr_chartIncl_self_isIso}; the transition isomorphisms
1558	  \(t_{I,J} : U^I_J \to U^J_I\) are the scheme-level transitions
1559	  \(\cref{def:gr_chart_transition}\), with identity field \(t_{\mathrm{id}}\)
1560	  supplied by \cref{lem:gr_chartTransition_self}.
1561	
1562	  The triple-overlap field \(t'\) and its first coherence obligation are supplied
1563	  by the two preceding results. The field itself is the morphism
1564	  \(t'_{I,J,K} : U^I_J \times_{U^I} U^I_K \to U^J_K \times_{U^J} U^J_I\) of
1565	  \cref{def:gr_chart_transition'}, and the compatibility field
1566	  \(t_{\mathrm{fac}}\) -- that \(t'\) is compatible with the projections to the
1567	  charts -- is \cref{lem:gr_chartTransition'_fac}, which reduces (both fibre
1568	  products being affine) to the ring identity
1569	  \cref{lem:gr_chartTransition'_ringIdentity} via the leg lemmas
1570	  \cref{lem:gr_awayPullbackIso_inv_fst} and \cref{lem:gr_awayPullbackIso_inv_snd}.
1571	
1572	  \emph{The residual cocycle obligation.} What remains is the \(t'\)-cocycle
1573	  field, the coherence
1574	  \[
1575	    t'_{I,J,K} \;\circ\; t'_{J,K,I} \;\circ\; t'_{K,I,J} \;=\; \mathrm{id}
1576	  \]
1577	  on the source triple overlap. Its categorical reduction is already
1578	  achieved: in the threefold composite, each of the two internal pairs of the
1579	  form \(\mathrm{ap}_{X,Y}^{-1} \circ \mathrm{ap}_{X,Y}\) -- the inverse of one
1580	  factor's target pullback identification against the next factor's source
1581	  pullback identification (\cref{def:gr_away_pullback_iso}) -- cancels, the two
1582	  identifications sharing the same instance because all three \(t'\)-factors are
1583	  built from the same construction (\cref{def:gr_chart_transition'}). Stripping
1584	  the outer conjugating pullback isomorphism (its two ends likewise cancel) and
1585	  collapsing the six remaining \(\Spec\)-arrows into a single \(\Spec\) leaves a
1586	  pure ring obligation: the identity of ring homomorphisms
1587	  \[
1588	    \Phi \;=\; \mathrm{id}_{\,R^I[1/(P^I_J P^I_K)]}, \qquad
1589	    \Phi \;:=\; \Theta_{I,J} \circ \mathrm{swap}_J \circ \Theta_{J,K}
1590	      \circ \mathrm{swap}_K \circ \Theta_{K,I} \circ \mathrm{swap}_I ,
1591	  \]
1592	  where \(\Theta_{X,Y}\) is the localised triple-overlap transition
1593	  (\cref{def:gr_cocycle_theta_ij}, taken for the rotated index triple) and each
1594	  \(\mathrm{swap}_X\) is the matching order-swap isomorphism
1595	  (\cref{def:gr_away_mul_comm_equiv}). This is a rotated analogue of the ring
1596	  cocycle condition \cref{lem:gr_cocycle}: it is proved by
1597	  reducing -- via the universal property of the away-localisation, applied to the
1598	  generators \(\mathrm{powers}(P^I_J P^I_K)\) -- to the chart-ring generators, and
1599	  then reusing the image-matrix cocycle computation
1600	  \cref{lem:gr_cocycle_imageMatrix_eq} (the same \((Y_K)^{-1} Y\) collapse that
1601	  underlies \cref{lem:gr_cocycle}). With this field in hand the glue datum is
1602	  complete: it is the structure \(\mathtt{Scheme.GlueData}\) with
1603	  \(U := \texttt{affineChart}\) (\cref{def:gr_affine_chart}),
1604	  \(V := \texttt{chartOverlap}\) (\cref{def:gr_chart_overlap}),
1605	  \(f := \texttt{chartIncl}\) (\cref{def:gr_chart_incl}),
1606	  \(t := \texttt{chartTransition}\) (\cref{def:gr_chart_transition}),
1607	  \(t_{\mathrm{id}} := \texttt{chartTransition\_self}\)
1608	  (\cref{lem:gr_chartTransition_self}),
1609	  \(t' := \texttt{chartTransition'}\) (\cref{def:gr_chart_transition'}),
1610	  \(t_{\mathrm{fac}} := \texttt{chartTransition'\_fac}\)
1611	  (\cref{lem:gr_chartTransition'_fac}), and the cocycle field above. The glued
1612	  scheme \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\) is then the colimit
1613	  \((\text{glue datum}).\mathrm{glued}\) produced by the gluing machine.
1614	
1615	  Moreover \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d) \to \Spec \mathbb{Z}\) is \emph{smooth of relative
1616	  dimension \(d(r-d)\)}. Smoothness and relative dimension are local on the
1617	  source; the charts \(\{U^I\}\) cover \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\), and each
1618	  \(U^I \cong \mathbb{A}^{d(r-d)}_{\mathbb{Z}}\) (\cref{def:gr_affine_chart}) is
1619	  affine space of dimension \(d(r-d)\) over \(\mathbb{Z}\), which is smooth over
1620	  \(\mathbb{Z}\) of relative dimension \(d(r-d)\) (the polynomial ring
1621	  \(\mathbb{Z}[x_1, \dots, x_{d(r-d)}]\) is a smooth \(\mathbb{Z}\)-algebra). As
1622	  the property may be checked on an open cover of the source, the conclusion
1623	  follows.
1624	\end{definition}
